The paper discusses a digital watermarking scheme that is both stego-secure and topologically secure, indicating a focus on information hiding and security. The evaluation of the Lyapunov exponent is also mentioned, suggesting a potential interest in chaos theory and dynamical systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
